channel.title: A working loader? And how to get the parameters?
channel.description:
Can anyone share with me a working loader, I can't get the parameters for an AppletStub because for some reason when I view the source of Runescape game page (world13.runescape.com/m0) it doesn't show the parameters or the <applet> tag. I've tried doing it through browser and other ways, one of them The Bank gave me, none of them worked. So could someone also tell me how you got the full source?
:cool:

item.title: A working loader? And how to get the parameters?
item.dc:creator: @moparisthebest Moparisthebest
item.description:
@moparisthebest wrote:

SourceForge

Cherokee

Download Cherokee for free. Cherokee is a fully extensible and scriptable automation engine for any and all java applets. To make it work for your favorite java applet the most you have to do is write is two classes.

That works, just check the latest version out from SVN. It also gets the parameters from the HTML, because it tells the server your browser doesn’t support javascript.
